# Whitelist approach: ignore everything by default, then re-include only the
# files the packaged extension actually needs at runtime.
#
# Note: vsce uses gitignore-style globs where `*` does NOT match dotfiles or
# recurse into subdirectories (shell glob semantics). Use `**` to match
# everything recursively.

# === Ignore everything recursively ===
**

# === Essential metadata ===
!package.json
!README.md
!LICENSE
!CHANGELOG.md

# === Built extension bundles ===
# Only the exact files produced by esbuild (see esbuild.js / esbuild.webview.js).
# Source maps, stale outputs (cli.js, http-server.js, *a.js), and the dist/web/
# and dist/test/ leftovers are intentionally NOT included.
!dist/**/*.js
